:QUOTE [subtitle:Paul Kalanithi, quotetype:PLAIN]
What makes life meaningful enough to go on living?

:JOURNEY
Reading When Breath Becomes Air
Section
Impact
- Medical training | 4 | Dense and human
- Diagnosis section | 5 | Register shifts
- Identity chapters | 5 | What matters
- Lucy's epilogue | 5 | Most devastating | Most powerful addition to any memoir I know

:NOW
Thinking about which of the questions Kalanithi raises about meaning I have actually \
tried to answer since I first read this, and which I have continued to defer.

:NOTE
This is not a sad book to avoid. It is a sad book to read. There is a difference, \
and the difference matters for knowing when to pick it up.
